==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Subalternate
<hw>Sub`al*ter"nate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Succeeding by turns; successive.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Subordinate; subaltern; inferior.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>All their <qex>subalternate</qex> and several kinds.</q>
<rj><qau>Evelyn.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Subalternate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Subalternate
<hw>Sub`al*ter"nate</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Logic)</fld> <def>A
particular proposition, as opposed to a universal one. See
<er>Subaltern</er>, 2.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Subalternating</ent>⟦br⟧
